c compliance practices is ramping up again.','Thu, 24 Jan 2013 10:07:47 -0500'),(59,'NCAA: Former staffers may have worked improperly with Shapiro attorney during Miami probe','<p><a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/ncaa-announces-problems-miami-investigation-180419822--spt.html\"><img src=\"http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/ETRaRYXNRIdG11.okNBMfQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/c8ea02d9ca947202270f6a706700c8f8.jpg\" width=\"130\" height=\"86\" alt=\"FILE - In this Jan. 17, 2013, file photo, NCAA President Mark Emmert speaks at the organization&#039;s annual convention in Grapevine, Texas. The NCAA is revealing that it has found &quot;an issue of improper conduct&quot; within its own enforcement program during its investigation into the compliance practices of Miami&#039;s athletic department. Emmert has ordered an external review of the enforcement program. Miami will not receive its notice of allegations until that review is complete. (AP Photo/LM Otero, File)\" align=\"left\" title=\"FILE - In this Jan. 17, 2013, file photo, NCAA President Mark Emmert speaks at the organization&#039;s annual convention in Grapevine, Texas. The NCAA is revealing that it has found &quot;an issue of improper conduct&quot; within its own enforcement program during its investigation into the compliance practices of Miami&#039;s athletic department. Emmert has ordered an external review of the enforcement program. Miami will not receive its notice of allegations until that review is complete. (AP Photo/LM Otero, File)\" border=\"0\" /></a>CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) â€” The NCAA&#039;s probe of Miami&#039;s athletic compliance practices is ramping up again.</p><br clear=\"all\"/>','Thu, 24 Jan 2013 09:51:13 -0500'),(60,'NCAA announces problems with Miami investigation','INDIANAPOLIS (AP) â€” The latest black eye for college sports belongs to the NCAA.','Wed, 23 Jan 2013 17:18:40 -0500');
